cwitools.params.parameterTypes¶

cwitools.params.parameterTypes = {'DEC_ALIGN': <class 'float'>, 'ID_LIST': <class 'list'>, 'INPUT_DIRECTORY': <class 'str'>, 'OUTPUT_DIRECTORY': <class 'str'>, 'RA_ALIGN': <class 'float'>, 'SEARCH_DEPTH': <class 'int'>, 'TARGET_DEC': <class 'float'>, 'TARGET_NAME': <class 'str'>, 'TARGET_RA': <class 'float'>}¶

dict() -> new empty dictionary dict(mapping) -> new dictionary initialized from a mapping object’s

(key, value) pairs

dict(iterable) -> new dictionary initialized as if via:

d = {} for k, v in iterable:

d[k] = v

dict(**kwargs) -> new dictionary initialized with the name=value pairs

in the keyword argument list. For example: dict(one=1, two=2)
